  <div class="node">
        <h2 class="title"><a href="/wheres-good-shared-calendar">Where&#039;s a good shared calendar?</a></h2>    <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Wed, 2007-05-02 19:38.</span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first taxonomy_term_40"><a href="/taxonomy/term/40" rel="tag" title="Internet economics, technology and issues" class="taxonomy_term_40">Internet</a></li>
<li class="last taxonomy_term_76"><a href="/tags/calendar" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_76 active">calendar</a></li>
</ul></span>
    <div class="content"><p>I really wish I could find a really good calendaring tool.  I&#8217;ve seen many of the features I want scattered in various tools, though some are nowhere to be found.   I thought it would be good to itemize some of them.  I&#8217;m mostly interested in *nix &#8212; I know that on Windows, MS Outlook is the most common choice, with Exchange for sharing. <span class='read-more'><a href="http://ideas.4brad.com/wheres-good-shared-calendar">&nbsp;read&nbsp;more&nbsp;&raquo;</a></span></p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; <ul class="links inline"><li class="first blog_usernames_blog"><a href="/blog/brad" title="Read brad&#039;s latest blog entries." class="blog_usernames_blog">brad&#039;s blog</a></li>
